msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.254:0.2"
msgid "26. Upasampadāvagga "
msgstr "26. Ordination "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.254:0.3"
msgid "254. Pañcamacchariyasutta "
msgstr "254. Five Kinds of Stinginess "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.272, sc1
msgctxt "an5.254:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, macchariyāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five kinds of stinginess. "

msgctxt "an5.254:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an5.254:1.3"
msgid "Āvāsamacchariyaṃ, kulamacchariyaṃ, lābhamacchariyaṃ, vaṇṇamacchariyaṃ, dhammamacchariyaṃ—"
msgstr "Stinginess with dwellings, families, material possessions, praise, and the teachings. "

msgctxt "an5.254:1.4"
msgid "imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca macchariyāni. "
msgstr "These are the five kinds of stinginess. "

#. VAR: paṭikuṭṭhaṃ → patikiṭṭhaṃ (bj, pts1) | patikkiṭṭhaṃ (s1-3, km) | paṭikiṭṭhaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an5.254:1.5"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ macchariyānaṃ etaṃ paṭikuṭṭhaṃ, yadidaṃ dhammamacchariyan”ti. "
msgstr "The most contemptible of these five kinds of stinginess is stinginess with the teachings.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.254:1.6"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

